summary:
This appears to be a product disclosure document for CitiFirst MINIs (a type of leveraged derivative product), not a standard ASX company announcement. Given the content, I'll extract the key structural components relevant to trading decisions:

Product Structure:
- Single Stock MINIs (long/short) with strike prices and stop-loss triggers for ASX-listed stocks (pages 1-29)
- Australian Index MINIs tracking ASX 200 futures (page 30)
- International Index MINIs tracking NDX, SPX, DJX, RTY, NKY (pages 31-32)
- Currency MINIs (AUD crosses) (pages 33-34) 
- Commodities MINIs (Copper, Gold, Silver, WTI Crude) (pages 35-36)

Key Features:
- Leveraged exposure (gearing % shown for each instrument)
- Stop-loss trigger levels provided for risk management
- All instruments effective June 20, 2025
- Standard interest rates: 
   * MINI Longs: 8.45% p.a. 
   * MINI Shorts: -0.15% p.a.
   * Index MINIs: 4.85% p.a.
   * Commodities MINIs: 4.85% p.a.

No actionable corporate actions, financial results, or capital markets events were identified in this product disclosure document. It is purely descriptive of derivative instruments.
